Enhances adhesion and survival of epithelial cells but decreases adhesion of mesenchymal cells (By similarity). Also plays a role in the induction of extracellular matrix (ECM) production and deposition independently of its nuclear translocation and binding to IGFs (PubMed:20345844, PubMed:26103640). Acts itself as a growth factor that can act independently of IGFs to regulate bone formation. Acts as a ligand for the ROR1 receptor which triggers formation of ROR1/HER2 heterodimer to enhance CREB oncogenic signaling (PubMed:36949068).
